0 nobly-born, if one recognize not one's own thought-forms, however learned
one may be in the Scriptures -- both Sutras and Tantras -- although practising
religion for a kalpa, one obtaineth not Buddhahood. If one recognize one's own
thought-forms, by one important art and by one word, Buddhahood is obtained.
